note first install maven open powershell as admisistor  ->
choco install maven -y
Step 1 — Create a project folder manually
cd C:\Users\rithi\Downloads
mkdir demoapp
cd demoapp

Step 2 — Create folder structure
mkdir -p src\main\java\com\example\demoapp
mkdir -p src\main\webapp\WEB-INF

Step 3 — Create a minimal pom.xml
notepad pom.xml


Paste this content and save:

<project xmlns="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0" 
         xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance"
         xsi:schemaLocation="http://maven.apache.org/POM/4.0.0 
         http://maven.apache.org/xsd/maven-4.0.0.xsd">

    <modelVersion>4.0.0</modelVersion>
    <groupId>com.example.demoapp</groupId>
    <artifactId>demoapp</artifactId>
    <version>1.0-SNAPSHOT</version>
    <packaging>war</packaging>

    <build>
        <plugins>
            <plugin>
                <groupId>org.apache.tomcat.maven</groupId>
                <artifactId>tomcat7-maven-plugin</artifactId>
                <version>2.2</version>
                <configuration>
                    <path>/</path>
                    <port>8080</port>
                </configuration>
            </plugin>
        </plugins>
    </build>

</project>

Step 4 — Create a simple JSP
notepad src\main\webapp\index.jsp


Paste this:

<h1>Welcome to Demo Web Project!</h1>
<p>This is for my practical.</p>


Save and close.

Step 5 — Optional: Create a Java class
notepad src\main\java\com\example\demoapp/App.java


Paste:

package com.example.demoapp;

public class App {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        System.out.println("Demo Web Project Running!");
    }
}

Step 6 — Compile the project
mvn compile

Step 7 — Run the web project
mvn tomcat7:run

Step 8 — Open in browser

Go to:

http://localhost:8080/demoapp


You’ll see:

Welcome to Demo Web Project!
This is for my practical.
